{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/variant\/refsink()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant\/VariantProtocol-Implementations"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"refSink"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"VariantRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" on a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"text":" with a floating reference","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"will convert the floating reference into a full reference.  Calling"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_ref_sink()"},{"text":" on a non-floating ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"type":"text","text":" results in an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"additional normal reference being added."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In other words, if the "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, then this call “assumes"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"ownership” of the floating reference, converting it to a normal"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference.  If the "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is not floating, then this call adds a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"new normal reference increasing the reference count by one.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All calls that result in a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" instance being inserted into a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"container will call "},{"code":"g_variant_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" on the instance.  This means"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that if the value was just created (and has only its floating","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference) then the container will assume sole ownership of the value"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"at that point and the caller will not need to unreference it.  This"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"makes certain common styles of programming much easier while still","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"maintaining normal refcounting semantics in situations where values"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"are not floating."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" uses a floating reference count system.  All functions with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"names starting with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_new_"},{"type":"text","text":" return floating"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"references.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant\/refSink()"},"metadata":{"externalID":"s:4GLib15VariantProtocolPAAE7refSinkAA0B3RefVSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib7VariantC","symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHea